4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, certain community foundation
6 entities are exempt from paying any state, county, and
7 municipal sales and use taxes through the 2026 tax
8 year.
9 This bill would revise the list of community
10 foundations that would be exempt from sales and use
11 taxes and would extend the state sales and use tax
12 exemptions through August 31, 2031.
13 This bill would allow municipalities and
14 counties to exempt these entities from local sales and
15 use taxes beginning September 1, 2026.
16 This bill would also repeal the law providing
17 for the existing sales and use tax exemptions for these
18 entities.
19
20
21 A BILL
22 TO BE ENTITLED
23 AN ACT
24
25 Relating to sales and use taxes; to add Section
26 40-9-39.41 to the Code of Alabama 1975, to exempt certain
27 community foundations from state sales and use taxes; to allow
28 municipalities and counties to exempt these entities from
Page 1

municipalities and counties to exempt these entities from
HB388 INTRODUCED
29 local sales and use taxes; and to repeal Section 40-9-39.4,
30 Code of Alabama 1975, regarding the existing community
31 foundation sales and use tax exemptions.
32 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
33 Section 1. Section 40-9-39.41 is added to the Code of
34 Alabama 1975, to read as follows:
35 §40-9-39.41
36 (a) All of the following community foundation entities
37 are exempted from paying any state sales and use taxes:
38 (1) The Black Belt Community Foundation.
39 (2) The Central Alabama Community Foundation.
40 (3) The Community Foundation of Greater Birmingham.
41 (4) The Community Foundation of Greater Decatur.
42 (5) The Community Foundation of Greater Huntsville.
43 (6) The Community Foundation of Northeast Alabama.
44 (7) The Community Foundation of South Alabama.
45 (8) The Community Foundation of West Alabama.
46 (9) The Limestone Area Community Foundation.
47 (10) The Walker Area Community Foundation.
48 (b) Each entity listed in subsection (a) shall file an
49 annual informational report in a manner as prescribed by the
50 Department of Revenue. The information on such reports shall
51 be consistent with the information required by the Department
52 of Revenue pursuant to Section 40-9-61 and rules adopted
53 thereunder. Information provided pursuant to this section is
54 exempted from the confidentiality provisions of Section
55 40-2A-10, and shall be provided by the Department of Revenue
56 to the Legislative Services Agency, Fiscal Division, on an
Page 2

to the Legislative Services Agency, Fiscal Division, on an
HB388 INTRODUCED
57 annual basis.
58 (c) The sales and use tax exemption authorized under
59 this section shall be effective September 1, 2026, and shall
60 continue through August 31, 2031.
61 (d) Any county or municipality may exempt the entities
62 listed in subsection (a) from county or municipal sales and
63 use taxes in accordance with Section 40-23-4.01.
64 Section 2. Section 40-9-39.4, Code of Alabama 1975,
65 relating to the existing sales and use tax exemptions for the
66 entities in Section 1(a), is repealed.
67 Section 3. Section 1 of this act shall become effective
68 immediately. Section 2 of this act shall become effective
69 January 1, 2027.
